    "biography": "<p>Resembling a vulture with a six-foot wingspan and razor-sharp claws, betrayer birds are encountered in small flocks of 1d6+1 birds. They seek out small or wounded parties in their territory and then try to lead predators and enemies to them in order to feast on the eventual leavings. They seem&nbsp;to have a positively human ability to identify suitable predators, though they fight with no more than bestial intelligence if directly attacked.</p>"
